d, United Kingdom":"Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Warrington, Cheshire, England":"Warrington, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1392–1435":"1392–1435","1389–1445":"1389–1445","1384–1440":"1384–1440","1420–1459":"1420–1459","1437–1500":"1437–1500","1450–Female":"1450–Overleden","1367–1433":"1367–1433","1372–1425":"1372–1425","16 November 1411":"16 november 1411","1440":"1440","1450":"1450","1384":"1384","1372":"1372","1392":"1392","1437":"1437","1459":"1459","1425":"1425","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1445":"1445","1433":"1433","1367":"1367","1389":"1389","17 October 1433":"17 oktober 1433","1420":"1420","3 February 1420":"3 februari 1420","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Utkinton, Cheshire, England":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Warrington, Cheshire, England":"Warrington, Cheshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1392–1435":"1392–1435","1389–1445":"1389–1445","1384–1440":"1384–1440","1420–1459":"1420–1459","1437–1500":"1437–1500","1450–Female":"1450–Deceased","1367–1433":"1367–1433","1372–1425":"1372–1425","16 November 1411":"16 November 1411","1440":"1440","1450":"1450","1384":"1384","1372":"1372","1392":"1392","1437":"1437","1459":"1459","1425":"1425","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1445":"1445","1433":"1433","1367":"1367","1389":"1389","17 October 1433":"17 October 1433","1420":"1420","3 February 1420":"3 February 1420","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Utkinton, Cheshire, England":"Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","Warrington, Cheshire, England":"Warrington, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Dutton","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English (Cheshire, Lancashire, and Staffordshire): habitational name from either Dutton in Cheshire or Dutton in Lancashire. The first is named from Old English <i>dūn</i> ‘hill’ + <i>tūn</i> ‘enclosure, settlement’; the second from the Old English personal name <i>Dudd(a)</i> (see   Dodd   1) + Old English <i>tūn</i>."],"variants":[{"name":"Dodd","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Dodd(e)</i>, <i>Dudd(e)</i>, Old English <i>Dodd(a)</i>, <i>Dudd(a)</i>, a name of uncertain origin which remained in fairly widespread and frequent use from Lincolnshire to Devon and from Essex to Lancashire in England until the 14th century.","English: nickname from Middle English <i>dod</i>, a word of uncertain meaning, possibly a ‘lumpish, thickset person’ (compare modern English dialect <i>dod</i> ‘bunch or heap’), or by extension a ‘foolish person’ (compare Middle English <i>dode-mused</i> ‘stupid’), or perhaps a derivative of <i>dodden</i> ‘to shave (the head), to trim (hair)’, hence ‘the hairless or close-cropped one’.","English: possibly a modern variant of <b>Daud</b> or <b>Dowd</b>, the former arising from the Middle English personal name <i>Daud(e)</i>, an extended form of   Daw  , and the latter from the Middle English personal name <i>Doude</i>, perhaps a side-form of either <i>Dodde</i> or of <i>Daude</i>, a pet form of   Ralph  ."]}]},{"name":"Elizabeth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["The usual spelling of   Elisabeth   in English. It is recorded in the medieval period, but was made popular by being borne by  Queen Elizabeth I  of England (  1533–1603 ). In the 20th century it again became extremely fashionable, partly because it was the name of  Elizabeth Bowes-Lyon  (  1900–2002 ), who in  1936  became Queen Elizabeth as the wife of King George VI, and after his death in  1952  achieved great public affection as Queen Mother for nearly half a century. Even more influentially, it is the name of her daughter  Queen Elizabeth II  (  b. 1926 )."],"variants":[{"name":"Elisabeth","meanings":["The spelling of   Elizabeth   used in the Authorized Version of the New Testament, and in most modern European languages. This was the name of the mother of John the Baptist (Luke 1:60). Etymologically, the name means ‘God is my oath’, and is therefore identical with <i>Elisheba</i>, the name of the wife of Aaron according to the genealogy at Exodus 6:23. The final element seems to have been altered by association with Hebrew <i>shabbāth</i> ‘Sabbath’."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Lady Elizabeth Dutton was born in 1392, in Dutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, her father, Lord Peter Dutton, was 25 and her mother, Elizabeth Butler, was 20. She married John Doane II on 16 November 1411, in Dutton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. She died in 1435, in Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 43."},"et":{"1392–1435":"1392–1435","1389–1445":"1389–1445","1384–1440":"1384–1440","1420–1459":"1420–1459","1437–1500":"1437–1500","1450–Female":"1450–Surnud","1367–1433":"1367–1433","1372–1425":"1372–1425","16 November 1411":"16. november 1411","1440":"1440","1450":"1450","1384":"1384","1372":"1372","1392":"1392","1437":"1437","1459":"1459","1425":"1425","1435":"1435","1500":"1500","1445":"1445","1433":"1433","1367":"1367","1389":"1389","17 October 1433":"17. oktoober 1433","1420":"1420","3 February 1420":"3. veebruar 1420","Dutton, Cheshire, England":"Dutton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Utkinton, Cheshire, England":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Utkinton, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Utkinton, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Warrington, Cheshire, England":"Warrington, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1392–1435":"1392–1435","1389–1445":"1389–1445","1384–1440":"1384–1440","1420–1459":"1420–1459","1437–1500":"1437–1500